  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-04 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 3. Seven factors are assessed with full gradation data; two factors (Numerical solver error, Use error) are flagged as 'beyond scope of current engagement' and left not-assessed, creating an epistemic gap that materially weakens credibility at MRL 3. Decision: Accepted.",
