      "acceptanceCriteria": "SQA plan documented, version control enforced, unit tests covering critical hemolysis subroutines.",
      "rationale": "SQA plan exists and version control is in place; however, unit test coverage for the hemolysis damage accumulation subroutine is incomplete, resulting in achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to Navier-Stokes and scalar transport equations; observed order of accuracy within 10% of theoretical.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification was performed on the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver and the passive scalar transport used for hemolysis index. Observed order of accuracy of 1.87 against theoretical 2.0 — within tolerance. Achieved level matches required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation applied; GCI reported for hemolysis index QoI; discretization error below 5% of predicted hemolysis index.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh Richardson extrapolation performed. GCI for hemolysis index at design point is 8.3%, exceeding the 5% target. Achieved level 2 against required level 3 due to insufficient mesh refinement budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid viscosity matched to within 2% of simulation boundary conditions.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump experimental conditions reproduced in simulation with flow rate deviation of 1.1% and rotational speed deviation of 0.8%. Fluid viscosity set to match blood analog within 1.5%. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Normalized hemolysis index predictions within 20% of experimental measurements across all 5 operating points; statistical comparison metric reported.",
      "rationale": "Predicted hemolysis index deviates from experimental data by 18–34% across the 5 operating points. Three of five points fall within 20%; two exceed the threshold. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) is the direct regulatory endpoint; no surrogate mapping required.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI — normalized index of hemolysis — is the same metric used in regulatory submissions. No surrogate transformation is applied. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments performed on the same pump geometry at overlapping operating conditions; patient blood rheology represented.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which matches the COU device class but not the specific commercial impeller geometry. Operating conditions overlap for 3 of 5 points. Blood analog rather than patient blood was used, reducing physiological fidelity. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated to residual tolerance of 1e-6 for all equations; round-off error analysis performed.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error characterization was identified as beyond the scope of the current engagement. The simulation team noted that iterative convergence logs were not retained in archival form and round-off error analysis was not performed within the project timeline. This factor is therefore not assessed; no required or achieved level can be assigned."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of simulation setup by a second analyst; checklist-based verification of boundary condition entry and material property assignment.",
      "rationale": "A second-analyst independent review of simulation setup was not conducted. The project schedule did not accommodate a formal use-error review process. This factor is considered beyond the current engagement scope and is not assessed; required and achieved levels are omitted."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by comparison to DNS or LES data for rotating confined flows; hemolysis constitutive model validated against cell-level damage data.",
      "rationale": "The k-omega SST turbulence model was selected based on prior literature for centrifugal pumps, but no direct comparison to higher-fidelity DNS or LES data was performed for this geometry. The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) is well-established but known to have significant uncertainty. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties and boundary conditions documented with sources; uncertainty ranges assigned to key inputs for Monte Carlo propagation.",
      "rationale": "Blood density, viscosity, and hemolysis model constants are documented with literature sources and uncertainty ranges. Monte Carlo sampling was performed over these inputs across 1000 realizations. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental sample characterization including blood analog lot traceability, temperature control records, and sample size justification.",
      "rationale": "Detailed characterization of the experimental test samples used in the FDA pump validation dataset was not available to the simulation team. Lot traceability and temperature control records for the blood analog fluid were not provided in the published dataset. This factor is not assessed as the necessary experimental metadata is outside the scope of the computational assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative mapping between experimental and simulation input parameters; any unmapped parameters identified with sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Primary hydraulic inputs (flow rate, rotational speed) are mapped quantitatively. However, wall roughness and inlet turbulence intensity are not directly measured in the experiment and were assigned nominal values without sensitivity analysis. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    }
